abstract: The company said it would deliver 70 to 85 of its newest jets this year but some of them would require extra work to fix manufacturing problems.
snippet: The company said it would deliver 70 to 85 of its newest jets this year but some of them would require extra work to fix manufacturing problems.
lead_paragraph: Boeing reported strong fourth-quarter results on Wednesday but forecast lower-than-expected profits for 2012 because of rising pension costs and the slow completion rate for its new 787 Dreamliner passenger jets.

headline.main: Boeing Posts 20% Profit Gain but Cuts Forecast for 2012 as Jet Completions Slow
headline.print_headline: Boeing Posts 20% Profit Gain but Cuts Forecast for 2012 as Jet Completions Slow
